g Options Private Non Confidential means that information disclosed by the student will be considered private but not confidential  Further  reports of sexual misconduct must be shared with appropriate administrators and the Title IX Coordinator so that the University can take necessary action to ensure the safety of the university community Title IX Coordinators nMichael Diaz  Title IX Coordinator nAmy Truelove  Deputy Title IX Coordinator nDanielle Earls  Deputy Title IX Coordinator The Title IX Coordinator will assist with filing a Title IX Report Contact  n               ntitleix uic edu nOffice for Access   Equity n    South Marshfield Avenue nRoom      M C      nChicago  IL            titleix uic edu Other Services  Office of the Dean of Students The Office of the Dean of Students provides support and assistance for student crime victims Contact  n              n     Student Services Building  SSB  n     West Harrison St  nChicago  IL       nFax                Learn more about services offered by the Office of the Dean of Students at  dos uic edu needhelp shtml dos uic edu needhelp shtml Other Services  Campus Security Authorities  CSAs CSAs will assist survivors  witnesses  or third parties with filing a report to be sent to the Title IX Coordinator and or UICPD Learn more about Campus Security Authorities at  https   clery uic edu campus safety security  https   clery uic edu campus safety security  The Jeanne Clery Disclosure of Campus Security Policy and Campus Crime Statistics Act  Clery Act   as amended  is a federal mandate requiring all institutions of higher education that participate in the federal student financial aid program to disclose information about crime on their campuses and in the surrounding communities  Campus Security Authorities are defined by the Clery act as campus officials who have significant responsibility for student and campus activities Reporting to Law Enforcement UIC Police Department  UICPD  n               n    West Maxwel